# Play HT

This is a simply generate TTS (Text to Speech) based on the text file.
It is using the [play.ht](https://play.ht/) API.

## Installation

```bash
pip install playht
```

## Usage

```python
from playht import PlayHT

if __name__ == '__main__':
    ht = PlayHT(
        user_id='',
        secret_key=''
    )
    ht.tts(text='Hello World', voice='larry', filename='hello_world.mp3')

    # or
    text_list = ht.get_words(filename='text.txt')

    for i, text in tqdm(enumerate(text_list)):
        ht.tts(text=text, index=i, output_folder='20230824', repeat=2)

```

